<div>
    <p>
        This plugin provides AI-powered analysis capabilities for Jenkins pipelines using the Codex CLI.
        It can analyze pipeline stages, steps, and script output to provide insights, suggestions, and automated responses.
    </p>
    <h3>Features</h3>
    <ul>
        <li>Pipeline step analysis using <code>codexAnalysis</code> step</li>
        <li>Stage-level analysis with automatic context gathering</li>
        <li>Script output analysis and interpretation</li>
        <li>Integration with Codex CLI and MCP servers</li>
        <li>Configurable analysis prompts and parameters</li>
        <li>Support for both Pipeline and Freestyle jobs</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Usage</h3>
    <p>
        Use the <code>codexAnalysis</code> step in your Pipeline scripts to analyze any content:
    </p>
    <pre><code>
pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'mvn clean compile'
                codexAnalysis(
                    content: 'Build completed successfully',
                    analysisType: 'build_analysis',
                    prompt: 'Analyze this build output and suggest improvements'
                )
            }
        }
    }
}
    </code></pre>
</div>
